Title : Neiraku Museum
Text : [[File:Isuien Nara18nt3200.jpg|thumb|Neiraku Museum]]
{{Nihongo|'''Neiraku Museum'''|寧楽美術館|Neiraku Bijitsukan}} is an [[art museum]] in the city of [[Nara, Nara|Nara]], central [[Japan]].<ref name=kotobank>{{cite web|title=Neiraku Bijutsukan|url=http://kotobank.jp/word/%E5%AF%A7%E6%A5%BD%E7%BE%8E%E8%A1%93%E9%A4%A8|work=Nihon no bijutsukan/hakubutsukan no index|publisher=Kōdansha|accessdate=13 May 2014}}</ref>

The museum opened in April 1969. It contains the works collected by Nakamura Junsaku (1875-1953), who was the founder of the [[Isuien Garden]]. The collection totals over 2000 items, which includes [[Bronzeware Script|bronze wares]], seals and mirrors of [[ancient China]] as well as pottery of [[History of Korea|ancient Korea]]. The museum building was built in a traditional style and features rotating exhibitions.

